    "Examples of Datasets for WatermarkingTo assess the performances of a deep learning-based watermarking scheme, different datasets were used in the literature.",
    "Among these datasets, we mention:• ImageNet: ImageNet is a widely used dataset in computer vision research, consisting of millions of labeled images across thousands of categories.",
    "While not specifically designed for watermarking, it can be used to evaluate the effectiveness of watermarking techniques on various types of images.• MS COCO (Microsoft Common Objects in Context): MS COCO is another popular dataset used for object detection and image segmentation tasks.",
    "It contains a large collection of images with diverse content, making it suitable for watermarking research.",
    "• BOSSbase (BOWS-2): BOSSbase is a benchmark dataset for digital image watermarking."
  ],
